What the verifier proves from logs/live rows:

```text
- LaunchAgent is loaded and running.
- Bridge script parses.
- LaunchAgent plist parses.
- Pentagon default model is gpt-5.5.
- The file-backed gauntlet log contains every easy/medium/hard/extra-hard
  hash, message id, trigger id, ACK id, reverse-trigger id, and proof path.
- The bridge runtime log contains every file-backed target trigger, ACK, and
  reverse-trigger id.
- The proof files contain the expected file-backed outputs.
- The live Pentagon DB has each target trigger and reverse trigger row, and all
  have completed_at.
- The live Pentagon DB has each ACK message row, and each ACK contains the
  expected gauntlet hash.
- The live Pentagon DB has active_graph agent rows, and all read back gpt-5.5.
```

What the verifier does not prove:

```text
- It does not prove the native Pentagon app poller is repaired.
- It does not prove a public/native trigger_turn tool exists.
- It does not prove target handoffs work without the external
  run.pentagon.trigger-bridge LaunchAgent.
```

JWT-expiry finding from logs:

```text
/Users/gaganarora/.pentagon/trigger-bridge.err.log showed a crash on:
GET /rest/v1/agent_triggers ... failed 401 PGRST303 JWT expired
```

Repair:

```text
scripts/pentagon-trigger-bridge.mjs now detects expired JWT responses, reloads
the current Pentagon session from run.pentagon.app.plist, and retries the
request once before failing. The same retry path is applied to mint-agent-token.
```

